{
  "version": "1",
  "_comment": [
    "Canonical surface manifest for aidoc-flow-ci (PLAN-004 PR-E).",
    "Enumerates every 1:1 template -> consumer-file mapping so install.sh",
    "--update, apply-standards.sh, and sync/check-drift.sh can walk ONE list",
    "instead of hardcoded per-script loops. Canon RULES stay in",
    "docs/REPO_STANDARDS.md; this file is only the machine-readable index (per",
    "PLAN-004 §6 R6). Two consumer surfaces are NOT 1:1 file copies and are",
    "handled outside this walk: labels.json (created via the GitHub API by",
    "install.sh's label step) and .pre-commit-config.yaml (canon block MERGED,",
    "not replaced, by install.sh). Re-run install.sh to refresh those.",
    "Fields: path=consumer path; template=default template under",
    "install/templates/; visibility_variants=per-visibility template override;",
    "substitute=de-branding placeholders install.sh substitutes at fetch time;",
    "safe_to_replace=--update --non-interactive may replace without prompting;",
    "auto_install=install.sh bootstraps it (false = optional adoption)."
  ],
  "files": [
    {
      "path": ".github/workflows/ai-review.yml",
      "template": "workflows/ai-review-public.yml",
      "visibility_variants": {"public": "workflows/ai-review-public.yml", "private": "workflows/ai-review-private.yml"},
      "substitute": [],
      "safe_to_replace": true,
      "auto_install": true
    },
    {
